Uses in Afghanistan
Originally, the Air Force released the videos with the aim of recruiting soldiers, and as the Department of Defense says, the contributions also serve the purpose of informing the population about the actual objectives of foreign deployments.
Such published propaganda is almost free of charge compared to conventional television commercials, defense expert Gordon Mackenzie told the BBC, but these videos always carry a certain degree of political message in themselves, as they entitle the existence of the military measures that have been decided by the government.
American Advertising with Game
But the army must also fight against amateur footage, which, in addition to the carefully edited, censored footage, also creates it on the net - such as those that show the death of the soldiers: in the somewhat hypocritical, "official" propaganda films, however, this is not at all said about the losses.
By the way, numerous videos of the war scenes in Iraq and Afghanistan have already been uploaded to the platform, but this “gatting” has only recently been discovered by the British.
The Americans, however, advertise in the somewhat different way, namely with the free downloadable shooter "America's Army", in which the player can slip into the soldier's skin as part of a more or less life-threatening simulation.
