Which insurance is best suited for me?
The motor vehicle insurance, which covers a possible damage caused by the driver, involves a high cost, the amount of which in turn depends on various factors, including age, gender, time of creation of the driver's license, family status, type of car to be insured.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, it has to be clear what we have to do with it here.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an insurer.
This agreement shall be established in writing by means of an insurance contract, which stipulates that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and, in return, is obliged to present the corresponding sum in the event of damage.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance, which consists of several factors, including age, gender, time of issue of the driver’s license, family status, type of vehicle to be insured or use.
The insurance companies set their prices in accordance with the statistics, so that in case of a higher risk of accidents, higher contributions will also be due.
For this reason, both over 25-year-olds and women have to make fewer contributions, because statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their caution.
The same is true for married persons, since according to the statistical values and consequently also according to the conviction of the companies, they tend to have fewer accidents than single ones.
The benefit attached to the vehicle affects the frequency of driving and thus also the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
When setting up the premium, the insurance companies must take into account a number of points.
For this reason, the driver also has to study the situation thoroughly in order to choose exactly the car insurance that best meets his personal needs.
At this point, we now list the most important points that should be considered when choosing an insurance in order to be able to make not only a performance, but also a price-oriented choice.
When choosing a low-cost insurance policy, those under the age of 25 meet numerous obstacles, such as low driving experience and a young driver’s license.
Even if it is best to complete full-cash insurance for an ideal insurance coverage, there are still cheaper alternatives.
Careful drivers can choose a full-casco with self-participation, so that the benefits of full-casco insurance are covered, but offered at a low price.
This type of contract implies that the customer must pay a portion of the amount resulting from the damage himself.
The amount is determined prior to the conclusion of the contract and based on the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher and lower the amount to be paid, explains Luis Noguera, Spain’s chief representative at First Europa, an online insurance brokerage company.
Another option is the extended insurance, which insures the customer against external accident damage, but not against the damages caused by the car itself.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's some advice.
If you’re under 25, it’s up to you to lower your insurance costs; this will increase your credit score by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the basic rate with the relevant insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment involves an increase in the said tariffs.
The amount of credits and penalty payments depends on the company and their income.
If the company has a profitable year behind it, it can afford to increase the bonus payments, Noguera explains.
Once the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to conclude a contract, which is due to the fact that with increasing driving practice, the accident rate decreases.
Thus, it makes the most sense to opt for full-cash insurance with self-participation.
Normally, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving, the Spanish head of the European company explains, and adds that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice after the fear of the beginning.
Nevertheless, for a married customer who does not have children, it is advisable to take out full cash insurance; of course, only if it also allows the financial situation of the respective person.
For insurers, married couples with children are considered the customers with the lowest accident rate, and consequently, their contribution payments are also low.
In this case, a full-cash insurance with self-contribution (at an amount of 300 euros) would be the best option. In case you have received a high credit, an extended insurance is recommended, which will only be used for the third year of the vehicle.
They drive more relaxed overall and have a larger purchasing power that allows them to impose a higher contribution payment, Luis Noguera notes.
For pensioners, it is offered to complete a full insurance with self-contribution (at an amount of 150 euros), or an extended insurance, which is used only with a sufficiently high credit.
Finally, it must be noted that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver from possible accident damage, but also because it carries high costs that require a thorough selection that corresponds to our personal situation.
